  <span id="freeText7753422801351331411" style="display:none">Contemplative and elegiac meditations on boundaries, memory, landscape, modernity inspired by Barghouti's return to Ramallah after 30 years of exile. His story is filled with both aesthetic and mundane revelations about daily life in the Palestinian occupied territories: Barghouti lays bare in deeply felt language the inseparability of the personal and the political.<br /><br />(edited because I can't spell.) </span>
