<div id="review_4169487859" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4169487859" />
    <a title="Sagheer Afzal" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4689352-sagheer-afzal"><img alt="Sagheer Afzal" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442511894p2/4689352.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4169487859?book_show_action=true">Aug 11, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sagheer Afzal" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sagheer Afzal" href="/user/show/4689352-sagheer-afzal">Sagheer Afzal</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781400032662" href="/book/show/846564.I_Saw_Ramallah">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4169487859" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1259753147443674412">It can be said that poets are best placed to convey the trauma of the displaced. This book is a poignant and eloquent insight into a people who through the machinations of friends and foes have become resigned to a bleak existence. Mourid does not accuse any one but neither does he spare any one. He doesn&apos;t connect events with a bloody line that has an arrow pointing at Jews. He simply tells it the way it is. And if you are to judge the Israel Palestine conflict through the lens presented in thi</span>
  <span id="freeText1259753147443674412" style="display:none">It can be said that poets are best placed to convey the trauma of the displaced. This book is a poignant and eloquent insight into a people who through the machinations of friends and foes have become resigned to a bleak existence. Mourid does not accuse any one but neither does he spare any one. He doesn't connect events with a bloody line that has an arrow pointing at Jews. He simply tells it the way it is. And if you are to judge the Israel Palestine conflict through the lens presented in this book then you can say the facts speak for themselves with tragic clarity. I will be reading 'Memoirs of a Jewish Extremist' to understand the other point of view. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1259753147443674412" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
