<div id="review_173024302" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/173024302" />
    <a title="Hiba Essa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3707170-hiba-essa"><img alt="Hiba Essa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1308913979p2/3707170.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/173024302?book_show_action=true">Jun 02, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hiba Essa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hiba Essa" href="/user/show/3707170-hiba-essa">Hiba Essa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781400032662" href="/book/show/846564.I_Saw_Ramallah">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer173024302" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2060955672064656029">First, Thank you Dubai Reader for lending me the book. I will definitely buy one to have it permanently in my shelf :) <br/><br/>I read this book in 3 days and I could have finished it sooner except I slowed down wanting to re read sentences and paragraphs which continued to give me the chills. <br/><br/>The writing is just too beautiful and touching, it would be inhuman to not feel his pain regardless of which side you are in. <br/>Personally, it made me look at my own country, family, loved ones and even the trees at </span>
  <span id="freeText2060955672064656029" style="display:none">First, Thank you Dubai Reader for lending me the book. I will definitely buy one to have it permanently in my shelf :) <br /><br />I read this book in 3 days and I could have finished it sooner except I slowed down wanting to re read sentences and paragraphs which continued to give me the chills. <br /><br />The writing is just too beautiful and touching, it would be inhuman to not feel his pain regardless of which side you are in. <br />Personally, it made me look at my own country, family, loved ones and even the trees at home differently. I took it all for granted simply because it was there whenever I cared to look... <br />His words... "our places have lost their meaning" gave me the chills. <br /><br />How do you not love that?! I have recommended this book to many. This book is timeless. I would definitely read it again. <br /><br />The only reservation i had was too many characters that didnt reappear in the story. I then decided that is besides the point of the book. <br /><br />My humble prayers goes out to each and every person in and out of Palestine affected by the Occupation in which ever way. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="2060955672064656029" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


